# WHAT IT IS
#   kproto is a "modern Kafka CLI" with first-class support
#   for protobuf-encoded messages.  The upstream pitch
#   compares it directly to `kcat` / `kafkacat`:
#     • Auto-detects matching protobuf schemas from a
#       `protos/` directory (no manual `--proto-path` lookup
#       required)
#     • Caches schema choices per topic in a `.kproto.yaml`
#       config (persistent setup)
#     • Pretty, compact, JSON, and JSONL output formats
#     • CSV / JSONL export
#     • Time-travel filtering: `--since 1h` /
#       `--from <ISO-timestamp>` / `--to <ISO-timestamp>`
#     • AWS MSK-native: built-in cluster discovery
#       (`--cluster <name|ARN>`) and IAM authentication
#       (default on)
#     • Confluent Schema Registry integration with optional
#       basic-auth credentials
#     • Content filtering with `--filter <text>`
#     • Pure TypeScript on top of kafkajs — no JVM required
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli.ts
#                       commander.js declarations; extracted
#                       via `gh api repos/jamesnixon197/
#                       kproto/contents/src/cli.ts`)
#
#   kproto <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Subcommands:
#     consume <TOPICS>...            Consume messages from one
#                                    or more Kafka topics
#                                    (positional args; space-
#                                    separated topic list)
#       -b, --brokers <BROKERS>        Kafka bootstrap brokers
#                                      (comma-separated; env
#                                      KAFKA_BROKERS)
#       -c, --cluster <NAME|ARN>       AWS MSK cluster name or
#                                      ARN (auto-discovers
#                                      brokers; AWS-only)
#       -g, --group <ID>               Consumer group ID
#                                      [default: kproto-
#                                      <timestamp>]
#       -f, --format <FMT>             Output format
#                                      (pretty | compact |
#                                       json | jsonl)
#                                      [default: pretty]
#       --from-beginning               Consume from beginning
#                                      of the topic
#       --no-headers                   Hide message headers
#       --show-binary-headers          Show full base64-encoded
#                                      binary headers
#                                      (default: compact)
#       --no-metadata                  Hide partition / offset
#                                      / timestamp metadata
#       --no-color                     Disable colored output
#       --filter <TEXT>                Filter messages
#                                      containing the given
#                                      text
#       --no-iam                       Disable IAM
#                                      authentication
#                                      (local dev override)
#       --region <REGION>              AWS region
#                                      [default: eu-west-1]
#       --protobuf                     Decode messages as
#                                      protobuf
#       --proto-path <PATH>            Protobuf schema file
#                                      (auto-detects if
#                                      omitted; env
#                                      PROTOBUF_PATH)
#       --message-type <TYPE>          Protobuf message type
#                                      (auto-detects if
#                                      omitted; env
#                                      PROTOBUF_MESSAGE_TYPE)
#       --clear-cache                  Clear cached schema for
#                                      the topic
#       --schema-registry <URL>        Schema Registry URL
#                                      (e.g.
#                                      http://localhost:8081;
#                                      env
#                                      SCHEMA_REGISTRY_URL)
#       --schema-registry-username <U>
#                                      Schema Registry
#                                      username  (env
#                                      SCHEMA_REGISTRY_
#                                      USERNAME)
#       --schema-registry-password <P>
#                                      Schema Registry
#                                      password  (env
#                                      SCHEMA_REGISTRY_
#                                      PASSWORD)
#       --since <TIME>                 Start consuming from
#                                      time ago (e.g.
#                                      `1h`, `30m`, `2d`)
#       --from <TIMESTAMP>             Start at absolute time
#                                      (ISO 8601)
#       --to <TIMESTAMP>               Stop at absolute time
#                                      (ISO 8601)
#       --max-messages <N>             Exit after N messages
#       --export <FMT>                 Export messages to file
#                                      (csv | jsonl)
#       --output <PATH>                Output file path
#                                      [default: messages-
#                                      <timestamp>.<FMT>]
#
#     topics                         List available topics
#       -b, --brokers <BROKERS>        Kafka brokers (env
